    <note type="biography">
        <p>American diplomat. Elected to the Massachusetts legislature as a Whig, 1840; led the state in opposition to slavery. Elected to Congress in 1858 and again in 1860 as a Republican. American minister to London, 1861–8. Published the papers and a biography of his father, the former president, John Quincey Adams (<hi rend="italic">DAB</hi>).</p></note>
